# Button - KX Dashboards

Original URL: https://code.kx.com/dashboards/button/

# Button

![Screenshot](../img/button/buttonhtmllight.jpg)  
_A Button_

## Set up

  1. Create a _Label_ for your button.

  2. Create the action or actions you want the button to control on click. 

## Basics

![Screenshot](../img/button/buttonbasics.png)

_Name_

    A name for the component provided by the user. 
_Label_

    Text to appear on the button
_Font Size_

    Size of button font in pixels
_Horizontal_

    Alignment of text inside the button
_Vertical_

    Alignment of text inside the button
_Tooltip_

    Descriptive tooltip to appear on button rollover
Button width

    When _Fixed Width_ is checked, the buton is _Width_ pixels wide, otherwise button fills width of the _Button_ component
_Icon_

    Select from list of icons to include in the button
_Is Enabled_

    Control whether a button is active or inactive; can be associated with a boolean Type [View State Parameter](../viewstateparameters/)

